title.narrative: IR 1.2 IMPROVED MOTHER AND NEWBORN HEA

description.narrative: By the end of 2014, increased coverage and quality of maternal and essential newborn care packages with focus on the post natal period using community based interventions, in identified vulnerable districts including in emergency settings, which contributes to Child Health, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Health And Emergencies, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: By 2014, high risk newborns, pregnant women and sick children have full access to, and utilize quality basic maternal, newborn, and child health services
